description.narrative: Governments have strengthened capacity for child rights-based policy formulation, planning and budgeting, particularly in target countries., which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Cross Sectoral - Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Gender Discriminatory Roles And Practices, Learning, Skills, Participation And Engagement, Reducing Child Poverty, Reducing Child Poverty (Covid), Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, children in the Pacific benefit from an improved policy environment and evidence-based planning and financing.

description.narrative: UNICEF Pacific continued to engage and strengthen partnerships with governments and United Nations agencies to influence child-sensitive policy formulation, planning, and budgeting. National youth climate action summits and youth parliaments provided effective platforms to amplify the voices of children and young people in Pacific Islands and Territories (PICTs) to influence national policies and plans. Costing of the National Strategic Plan in the Marshall Islands will also inform the formulation of social sector budgets in favor of children | Status:On-track | As-of Date:03/02/2022
